<h2>Demography and Population Studies</h2><p>
	<div id="column2_text" class="scrollable">
          <a href="http://www.censtatd.gov.hk/home/index.jsp">Hong Kong</a> - Census and Statistics Department.<br>
          <a href="http://www.singstat.gov.sg/">Singapore</a> - Singapore National Statistics Office.<br>
          <a href="http://www.censusindia.net/">Official Web site of Census of India</a> - Census data, plans for India's Census in 2001, and statistical reports and maps of India.<br>
          <a href="http://www.lse.ac.uk/Depts/spa/bsps/">The British Society for Population Studies</a> - The main objectives of the Society are to further the scientific study of biological, economic, historical, medical, social and other disciplines connected with human populations. <br>
          <a href="http://www.bib-demographie.de/">Bundesinstitut für Bevölkerungsforschung (BiB)</a> - The site of the German Federal Institute for Population Research contains information on population research in Germany (both in German and English). <br>
          <a href="http://www.ciemi.org/">Centre d'information et d'études sur les migrations internationales (CIEMI)</a> - Documentation library, reports and books on internal and international migration (in French, English and Italian). <br>
          <a href="http://www.nsd.uib.no/cessda/">Council for European Social Science Data Archives</a> - CESSDA promotes the acquisition, archiving and distribution of electronic data for social science teaching and research in Europe. <br>
          <a href="http://popin.natur.cuni.cz/">Czech Republic Population Information (POPIN Czech Republic)</a> - Provides information on national population trends and population research. Time series of population statistics and indicators are available. <br>
          <a href="http://www.suda.su.se/">Demography Unit (SUDA)</a> - Information about the activities of the Stockholm University Demography Unit. <br>
          <a href="http://www.dsw-online.de/">Deutsche Stiftung Weltbevölkerung</a> - Activities and objectives of the German Foundation for World Population. (in German and English) <br>
          <a href="http://www.emin.geog.ucl.ac.uk/">European Migration Information Network</a> - A database of information relating to international migration. <br>
          <a href="http://www.diba.cat/inici">European Youth Observatory</a> - Comparative data about the situation of young people in different cities in Europe, reports, information about practices, and documents related to youth and youth policy in the different cities and regions of the network. <br>
          <a href="http://www.hips.hacettepe.edu.tr/">Hacettepe University Institute of Population Studies</a> - The site of the Turkish Institute of Population Studies contains information on population research in Turkey (both in Turkish and English). <br>
          <a href="http://www.infostat.sk/">INFOSTAT Bratislava</a> - Analysis and forecasting population development. <br>
          <a href="http://www.ined.fr/">Institut National d'Études Démographiques (INED)</a> - This site of the French national demographic institute contains extensive information on population research in France (both in French and English); the library database can be searched via the Web. <br>
          <a href="http://www.iss.nl/">International Institute of Social Studies (ISS)</a> - International centre of social science education and research in The Hague, The Netherlands. <br>
          <a href="http://econ.worldbank.org/WBSITE/EXTERNAL/EXTDEC/EXTRESEARCH/EXTLSMS/0,,contentMDK:21610833~pagePK:64168427~piPK:64168435~theSitePK:3358997,00.html">Living Standards Measurement Study</a> - (LSMS) household surveys. The Development Economics Research Group (DECRG) of the World Bank, formerly the Policy Research Department. <br>
          <a href="http://www.demogr.mpg.de/">Max Planck Institute for Demographic Research</a> - Produces basic, scientific research on selected demographic questions. The website presents information on the institute, research topics and publications. <br>
          <a href="http://www.nidi.nl/">Netherlands Interdisciplinary Demographic Institute (NIDI)</a> - NIDI is an independent Dutch national institute engaged in scientific study of population. The website presents research projects, Dutch population figures, publications and links to other population sites. <br>
          <a href="http://www.network-migration.org/">Network Migration</a> - A cooperation between people and institutions aiming to promote knowledge and understanding of migration in Europe. <br>
          <a href="http://www.nom-nos.dk/">Nomesco / Nosesco</a> - Nordic medico and social statistical committees. <br>
          <a href="http://www.nsd.uib.no/english/">Norwegian Social Science Data Services</a> - Research projects and related publications in the social sciences, the humanities, medicine, environment and development research by the Norwegian research community. <br>
          <a href="http://www.valt.helsinki.fi/sosio/pru/">Population Research Unit (PRU)</a> - at the Department of Sociology, University of Helsinki, Finland. <br>
          <a href="http://www.wpf.org/">World Population Foundation (WPF)</a> - Information on this Dutch non-profit organisation working for the improvement of reproductive and sexual health in development countries (both in  English and Dutch) <br>
          <a href="http://www.measuredhs.com">Measure DHS</a> - Data collection for evaluation needs of host countries. Population and facility-based surveys, secondary data analyses, and research using qualitative, education, and gender-based studies. <br>
          <a href="http://www.prb.org/">Population Reference Bureau</a> - Information on population estimates and key indicators for all members of the UN and areas with populations of or greater than 150,000. <br>
          <a href="http://www.library.uu.nl/wesp/populstat/populhome.html">Population Statistics</a> - Summarized population trends over time by country and by regions within countries. <br>
          <a href="http://www.photius.com/rankings/population.html">Population Statistics</a> - Population statistics by country: total population, growth rate, birth rate, death rate, migration rate, life expectancy, infant mortality, and population density. <br>
          <a href="http://www.un.org/popin/">United Nations Population Information Network</a> - Links to publications and conferences. <br>
          <a href="http://www.stat.gouv.qc.ca/default_an.htm">Quebec Institute of Statistics</a> - Provides economic, social and census data about the province of Quebec. <br>
          <a href="http://www.statcan.ca/">Statistics Canada</a> - In depth population statistics including the Canada 2001 census. <br>
          <a href="http://www.census.gov/">United States Census Bureau</a> - Demographic information and analyses.</div>
